This article is a presidential proclamation issued by President Barack Obama on June 18, 2010, declaring June 20, 2010, as Father's Day in the United States. The proclamation highlights the importance of the bond between fathers and children, acknowledging their role as teachers, coaches, mentors, and role models. It emphasizes the positive impact of active and committed fathers on the lives of their children and the challenges faced by children and families when fathers are absent. The proclamation also recognizes the diverse forms of nurturing families and expresses gratitude to parents serving in the United States Armed Forces. The article concludes by calling upon all citizens to observe Father's Day with appropriate programs, ceremonies, and activities to honor fathers, both living and deceased.